diff:1667787987:1667588082:=53,69c53%0a%3c #foxbegin 221107-022627-589760#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!Major improvements in treatment of the deaf community %0a%3c -> - kramesh%0a%3c -> [-06.11.2022 - 18:26-]%0a%3c >>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a%3c (:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a%3c {[foxdelrange button 221107-022627-589760 {$FullName} ]}%0a%3c (:if1end:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c Being able to computerize sign language would be extremely beneficial to members of the deaf community who struggle with lack of access to sign language resources. Especially with the pandemic, it probably became difficult for many deaf people who might have relied on being in person to clearly see sign language or read lips. Being able to use machine learning and combine technology with linguistics could improve many lives. For example, those who don’t know sign language could use technology to communicate with those who use sign language to communicate. Hopefully, this new software will be accessible to people around the world.%0a%3c %0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 221107-022627-589760#%0a---%0a> %0a
