researchers to use knowledge from other computer vision tasks like object recognition to help build classifiers for signs. By leveraging pretrained models, researchers need smaller labeled sign datasets and less compute to achieve the same level of recognition accuracy. %0a%3c %0a%3c In 2007, team from the University of Washington used transfer learning to recognize signs from multiple perspectives. Their research was able to boost model accuracy by over 3%25 by transferring model weights from one perspective to another. When combined with larger and larger datasets- such as 25,000 annotated sign videos released by Microsoft in 2019- I expect transfer learning will be an essential part of making automated sign language recognition accessible to everyone.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c You must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)%0a%3c !!Change article category%0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#changearticlecategory:)%0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:Section: D:)%0a%3c (:Category: SignLanguage:)%0a%3c (:Title: Sign Language Recognition:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
